metadata.name: Infinite Skies
metadata.description:
It only takes a look into the night sky to realise just how small we really are.

This cold, still night on the shores of Lake Pedder in Tasmania, gives a glimpse into the raw beauty of nature and a window into whatâ€™s out there in the universe.

The buzzing of satellites overhead, a constant reminder of the fascination the human race has with the cosmos and our determination to explore the infinite vastness to unlock its many secrets.
